==English==
===Etymology===
[[w:Greek language|Greek]][[Category:Greek derivations]] ''lēmma'', "auxiliary proposition".
===Noun===
'''lemma''' (''plural:'' '''[[lemmata]]''' ''or'' '''[[lemmas]]''')

# {{mathematics}} A proposition proved or accepted for immediate use in the proof of some other proposition.
# {{linguistics}} A canonical form of a term, particularly in the context of highly inflected languages.

